cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NA 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as the bilateral filter is commonly used in image processing and computational photography. It may also belong to the computer graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as the filter is used for smoothing in graphics applications. The use of approximation techniques suggests that it may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The mention of operations per pixel suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of Gaussian kernels suggests that it may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
